        <abstract> 
<p>RLT’s two articles in <hi rend="italic">Spectator</hi> [4 Mar and 25 Mar 1876] greatly honour CD.</p> 
            <p>Tait has made a good point about "Survival of the Fittest".</p>
            <p>Dr Rudinger’s extensive inquiries show that all eminent German surgeons are unanimous about non-growth of extra digit after amputation.</p> 
<p>J. Kollmann has written regretting CD has given up atavism and extra digits [in 2d ed. of <hi rend="italic">Variation</hi>]; gives new evidence of a rudimentary sixth digit in batrachians.</p> 
        </abstract>
